channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Trump thanks 'outstanding' law enforcement after apparent assassination attempt
item.description: Former President Donald Trump thanked law enforcement for their "incredible" response to what the FBI has described as an assassination attempt.

item.title: Mortgage and refinance rates today, September 16, 2024: Should you wait until after Wednesday to buy a home?
Ober 30 killed in Mexico after cartel leaders arrested in U.S
item.description: The clashes follow the arrests on U.S. soil of Sinaloa Cartel co-founder Ismael "El Mayo" Zambada, as well as Joaquin Guzman Lopez, a son of El Chapo.

item.title: Tito Jackson dead at 70, 'heartbroken' children confirm
item.description: Tito Jackson -- a member of The Jackson 5 and brother to Michael Jackson and Janet Jackson -- died aged 70, his children confirmed on social media.

item.title: Kremlin on alleged Trump shooter's Ukrainian links: playing with fire has consequences
China frees 68-year-old U.S. pastor David Lin after 18 years in prison
item.description: A Chinese court sentenced U.S. pastor David Lin to life in prison in 2009, but he's been released ahead of China's Thanksgiving-like Mid-Autumn Festival.

item.title: Tropical storm warning is issued for parts of the Carolinas
item.description: A tropical storm warning has been issued for a stretch of the Southeast seacoast from a disturbance forecasters say is likely to become a tropical storm in coming hours

item.title: Ukraine asks UN, ICRC to join humanitarian effort in Russia's Kursk region
Idaho murders suspect jailed 300 miles from crime after trial moved
item.description: Bryan Kohberger is charged with four counts of murder in the deaths of Ethan Chapin, Xana Kernodle, Madison Mogen and Kaylee Goncalves.

item.title: What the 911 calls in Georgia high school shooting reveal
item.description: The emergency dispatch center that received active shooter reports from a Georgia high school was overwhelmed with 911 calls as the situation unfolded.

item.title: ‘He forced me to take Social Security at 62’: My husband inherited millions, but never gave me a penny. If I divorce him, would I get any of it?
Tito Jackson, Michael's brother and member of Jackson 5, dies at 70, sons say
item.description: Tito Jackson, Michael's brother and one of the brothers who made up the beloved pop group the Jackson 5, has died at age 70, his sons say.

item.title: More threats in Springfield, Ohio: College closes campus as fear grips community
item.description: A new bomb threat prompted officials Sunday at Clark State College in Springfield, Ohio, to close the campus this week and hold classes virtually, the school said.

item.title: Europe's EV troubles bubble up at Brussels Audi factory
Rural North Carolina county set to reopen hospital with federal help
item.description: One rural North Carolina county is on track to be among the first where a hospital reopens owing to a new federal hospital classification meant to help save small, struggling facilities.
